info.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 14 at 6:22AM PST until January 14 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...South winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts to 45 mph. Locally stronger gusts over ridgetops and exposed terrain. * WHERE...Northern Humboldt Coast, Southwestern Humboldt, and Northern Humboldt Interior. * WHEN...Until 4 PM this afternoon. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS... Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
